    <help><![CDATA[
        Teloscope (from telomeres and telescope) is a tool for telomere annotation in genome assemblies. 
        It scans for user-specified and canonical patterns across assembly paths, contigs and windows.
        Teloscope annotates terminal and interstitial telomeres, canonical/noncanonical matches and genome-wide metrics such as GC content, Shannon entropy, and repeat counts.
        Finally, it generates a detailed telomere summary report for paths, telomere statistics, and chromosome labels to assess telomere completeness.
        Teloscope can be used for both complete and fragmented assemblies, providing valuable information for genome manual curation and analysis.
    ]]></help>
